title: Grateful Dead Live at West High Auditorium on 1980-06-19
description: Alabama Getaway-> Promised Land, They Love Each Other-> El Paso, Tennessee Jed, Cassidy, Althea-> Looks Like Rain, Far From Me, The Music Never Stopped China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider-> CC Rider, Peggy-O, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums-> Wharf Rat-> I Need A Miracle-> Bertha-> Good Lovin', E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: This is pretty clean. A little too much treble and vocals stand out a bit much. Nice Peggy-O and Bertha. Pretty average performance.

ALaska '80 This has gone down as quite a fine run for the boys, altho this seems to be the warm-up. Nothing stellar here, and the audio is mixed very heavy on the high-end. Look at the two latter performances for the high octane!

Alaska 1980 I love all three shows at this venue.  The boys play better each night culminating in a fantastic performance on 6/21.  This is a nice show.  There are problems with the vocals and clipping in some instances.  This show is worth the download.  The China/Rider is done very well. Enjoy
nice I really enjoy the slowness of Althea!!

worth a listen i threw this show on not knowing what to expect. I was pretty amazed at how tight they were, and Jerry was especially articulate and in control, which i love. Bobbys vocals even his backups were rich and strong. 

The solo in They love each other nearly blew away. 

I dont know, I dug it. worth a listen.
